column5: Thx
We've been going to his lakes since before he was there. But for some reason he isn't returning calls or answering emails. I'm just wondering if anyone has heard from him regarding next year. Thanks
Ok gotcha,can't help you out,just gotta keep trying all's you can do.
Have you fished either Murdock or thicketwood with cff?
I fished Thicketwood twice several years ago and it was great. Lots of big walleye. Since then we've been to Job and it's also great. The cabins are really nice old log cabins.
Thanks,I'll have to book with him sometime.hope you hear from him.
Whose Wayne Gretzke
He won a award for Walmart's most trusted worker in Canada.
Any info on the status of Canadian Flyin Fishing would be appreciated.
Sorry Robbie.Have nothing for you.Never even heard of that place.Where is it
Out of Red Lake
Has anyone heard from Josh Varickanickal with CFF?
Sure doesn't look like a Canadian name,is he the owner?
what's a Canadian name 🤣
Yes he owns the original Canadian fly in fishing out of Red Lake. He purchased it from Diane Manning a few years ago.
We are booked into one of his camps this coming year but I've been unable to reach him since July.
Wayne Gretzky n john jakobs,there both Canadian icons
You forgot Shania Twain
Thanks for high jacking my post!
Didn't forget about shania,keeping her for myself

Sry about the high jacking,I've only talked to josh on the phone a few times about his lakes,seems like he does well,booked up most of time,I don't know anyone who has fished his lakes that are on WC,looke like he has some awesome outposts.Good luck if you go with him,I would be interested in your report back.
